abstract: Voters in Kazakhstan re-elect Pres Nursultan A Nazarbayev with 98 percent of vote and 95 percent voter turnout.
lead_paragraph: Nursultan A. Nazarbayev, who has governed the country since the Soviet Union collapsed, secured his fifth term with 97.7 percent of the vote.

headline.main: Kazakhstan’s President Is Re-elected by Almost Every Voter
headline.print_headline: World Briefing | Asia; Kazakhstan: President Wins New Term, Shrugging Off ‘Superdemocratic’ Critics
